Johannesburg - A popular local actress was shot and injured at her Joburg home on Wednesday morning. Paramedics confirmed that she was recovering in hospital and remains in a serious but stable condition.Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha said an armed gang entered her Randburg home just after midnight. Reports from the scene indicate that several gunmen had entered the premises of a popular actress, shots were fired and she sustained two serious gunshot wounds, Botha said, adding that they found her in a serious but stable condition. The patient was treated at the scene and then transported to a specialised hospital under the constant care of an Advanced Life Support paramedic, he said. Exact details to the incident and preceding events will however remain a subject for police comment.&quot;The actress' identity was not yet known as police had not released her name.The Star